article.description: Kopriva scores 19, George Washington beats Fordham
article.headline: Kopriva scores 19, George Washington beats Fordham
article.linkText: Kopriva scores 19, George Washington beats Fordham
article.story: NEW YORK -- John Kopriva scored 19 points, and Patricio Garino added 16 and eight rebounds to help George Washington beat Fordham 79-59 on Thursday night. Kethan Savage scored 14 while Joe McDonald and Kevin Larsen added 11 apiece for George Washington (15-4, 5-1 Atlantic 10), which has won nine of its last 10 games. A 3-pointer by Garino gave the Colonials an 18-2 lead with 14:38 left in the first half as Fordham made just one of its first nine field goal attempts. George Washington made 17 of 24 (70.8 percent) field goals in the first half and scored the first 10 points of the second to push its lead to 51-27 with 16:37 to play. Six-straight points by Eric Paschall pulled Fordham (5-10, 0-6), which has lost six in a row, within 10 with four minutes left. Paschall led the Rams with 17 points. Mandell Thomas added 15 points, eight rebounds, five assists and three steals.
